\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Search trajectories of \textsc  {FuseTune}{} on a stylized validation surface in $(\log \lambda ,\log \gamma )$ space. Contour lines represent cross-validation RMSE levels; darker shading indicates lower (better) values. (a)~The $\ell _1$ branch starts at the box center and navigates via axis-aligned coordinate moves with nonmonotone acceptance. (b)~The $\ell _2$ branch starts from a \texttt  {glmnet}-derived $\lambda $ seed, screens a small set of $\lambda $ candidates at low $\gamma $, refines $\gamma $ vertically, and adjusts $\lambda $ only when justified.}}{5}{figure.caption.3}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:concept}{{1}{5}{Search trajectories of \method {} on a stylized validation surface in $(\log \lambda ,\log \gamma )$ space. Contour lines represent cross-validation RMSE levels; darker shading indicates lower (better) values. (a)~The $\ell _1$ branch starts at the box center and navigates via axis-aligned coordinate moves with nonmonotone acceptance. (b)~The $\ell _2$ branch starts from a \texttt {glmnet}-derived $\lambda $ seed, screens a small set of $\lambda $ candidates at low $\gamma $, refines $\gamma $ vertically, and adjusts $\lambda $ only when justified}{figure.caption.3}{}}
