\newlabel{fig:synth_family}{{3}{9}{Synthetic family comparison by normalized gain per second. The \(\ell _1\) panels show a clear efficiency advantage for \codeid . The redesigned \(\ell _2\) panels show the same pattern in \texttt {fusion\_helpful\_chain} and a strong cost-quality compromise in the other two families}{figure.caption.10}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces \(\ell _2\) validation-surface diagnostics for two representative datasets. (a)~shows per-fold marginals together with their across-fold means; (b)~shows single-fold marginals. In both cases the preferred regularization regime is not stable across datasets: \texttt  {school\_ilea} pushes the optimum toward very weak fusion, while \texttt  {beijing\_air\_quality} favors a clearly positive fusion level.}}{9}{figure.caption.11}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:surface_diag}{{4}{9}{\(\ell _2\) validation-surface diagnostics for two representative datasets. (a)~shows per-fold marginals together with their across-fold means; (b)~shows single-fold marginals. In both cases the preferred regularization regime is not stable across datasets: \texttt {school\_ilea} pushes the optimum toward very weak fusion, while \texttt {beijing\_air\_quality} favors a clearly positive fusion level}{figure.caption.11}{}}
